com.twitter.heron.common.utils.tuple

Class TickTuple

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.twitter.heron.common.utils.tuple.TickTuple
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Tuple

    public class TickTuple
extends java.lang.Object
implements Tuple
    This is the tick tuple as seen by the bolt. where each value can be any type. Tuples are dynamically typed -- the types of the fields do not need to be declared. Tuples have helper methods like getInteger and getString to get field values without having to cast the result.

    Heron needs to know how to serialize all the values in a tuple. By default, Heron knows how to serialize the primitive types, strings, and byte arrays. If you want to use another type, you'll need to implement and register a serializer for that type.

    See Also:
    Storm serialization
